channel.title: Kinda weird
channel.description: Im Saint from Rune-Server (I doubt any of you go there due to the hatred, and tbh its an idiotic community at best due to the immaturity level) But this was actually the first website for RSPS I joined back in the day. I was about 11 at the time, so i couldn't spell anything. I couldn't even spell my favorite anime character from back in the day (Tsukasa) lol. So I forgot my user for about 6 years, and tried some of my old emails today and it worked. Just thought I'd post and say hi after 6 and a half years of inactivity on this website.

The only difference is the general value each member has on either forum. On here, people cannot stand being spoken out against, even if it was factual information. In other words, people have really big egos here. On R-S, people value nothing but money, which automatically gives them the assumed right of talking nonsense to every other member.

I love this community, and it is a resort for me to learn about RS2 emulation and other programming information; however, it seems like no one here can have an opinion without someone else calling you out for it.
